<article class="task exercise-like"><h5 class="heading">
<span class="type">Task</span><span class="space"> </span><span class="codenumber">a</span><span class="period">.</span>
</h5>
<p>Show that in general, if we let <span class="process-math">\(\int\dx{v}=v+a\)</span>  in the integration by parts formula, then we will obtain the same result as before, namely <span class="process-math">\(\int u\dx{v}=uv-\int v\dx{u}\text{.}\)</span></p></article><span class="incontext"><a href="section-5.html#task-18" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
